          "description": "Here the River of Bruenor's Woe turns west and begins its drop into the forested valley where it metamorphoses into the Brown River. From the southwest, you hear the roar of falling water and spot small clouds of mist as they dissolve in the air above point where the river vanishes. The banks are too steep to the south for you to enter, but you could enter just east of here. Trees rise to your west, offering another possible path to the river.",
