          "vnum": 57016,
          "name": "Northern Slopes of the River Valley",
          "description": "Surrounded by knee-high grasses, you stand on a mild slope rolling gently down into the Brown River valley to the south. A ways east, a dense forest springs up out of the ground and obscures the course of the river. A second hill rises beyond the river to the south. You can travel uphill to the north, downhill to the south, or through the grasses to the edge of the forest just east of here. A trail also runs west.",
